      "raw_text": "on the granting of public utility\nfranchises.\n\n\n1t is known that several council\nmen will support the ordinance and\nthe actions of the others will be\nwatched with interest. The ordi.\nnance may come up before the\ncommittee of the whole this eve\nming, but no particular time has\nbeen set for a hearing of the ad-\nvocates of the new law. The refer\nendum supporters believe that the\nordinance will be opposed by the\ncorporate interests of the city who\nrealize that they cannot cajole all\nthe voters of the city to grant pub\nlie franchises worth many thou\nsands for nothing in return."
